│ nullptr).                                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ Actually, looking more carefully at the problem: The issue is that we're trying to create a MemoryAccess for an instruction that doesn't touch memory. This shouldn't happen. The original instruction         │
│ shouldn't have a MemoryAccess if it doesn't touch memory.                                                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ But the check in `cloneInstructionInExitBlock` is: `if (MSSAU.getMemorySSA()->getMemoryAccess(&I))`. If this returns true, it means the original instruction has a MemoryAccess. So we assume the cloned       │
│ instruction also needs one.                                                                                                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ The bug might be that the original instruction was incorrectly given a MemoryAccess. Or, the instruction might have had a MemoryAccess when it was created, but later transformations changed it (e.g., added  │
│ `memory(none)` attribute).                                                                                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ I think the proper fix is to make `createMemoryAccessInBB` robust to the case where the instruction doesn't need a MemoryAccess. We should:                                                                    │
